                "display_name": "v78",
                "accept_rate": 93
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1475352015,
            "creation_date": 1475351713,
            "body": "<p><strong>complexity : log (n)<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>Explanation: <\/p>\n\n<p>If you look at the binary notation of n and g(n).<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>*****0 =&gt; ***** (left shift)\n*****1 =&gt; ****0 (change last 1 to 0) =&gt; **** (left shift) \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>So, it reduces one bit per 2 iterations in the worst case running time.<\/p>\n\n<p>So total number of operations: <strong>2*log<sub>2<\/sub>(n)<\/strong> = <strong>O( log<sub>2<\/sub>(n) )<\/strong>  .<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 39810883,
            "question_id": 39810561,
            "last_edit_date": 1475352015
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cd15432646ae9295a5062d736d913aeb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 444029,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 835611,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/835611/user835611",
                "reputation": 2571,
                "display_name": "user835611"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1505569211,
            "creation_date": 1505569211,
            "body": "<p><code>O(lg(n))<\/code>: If the input is a power of 2, every call divides by 2, which is obviously <code>lg(n)<\/code>. For any other input, at least every second operation divides by 2 (if one operation subtracts one, the input was off before and is now even). So there are at most <code>2*log(n)<\/code> operations, which is <code>O(lg(n))<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 46254521,
            "question_id": 39810561
        }
